 <VARNAME>C14033_1</VARNAME>
 <SENTIMENT>Mixed</SENTIMENT>
 <VALUE>Very well. I would suggest that you ask physical therapy guys to calm down. They come in strong, rush people to their feet without noticing low blood pressure and push you too fast too soon. An extra hour of recovery made a huge difference this time around (as opposed to prior knee replacement). The previous time I almost fainted and came very close to vomiting. This time, with some rest and better blood pressure, it was a breeze.</VALUE>
