 <VARNAME>SECTCARE</VARNAME>
 <SENTIMENT>Positive</SENTIMENT>
 <VALUE>I wanted to take a moment to share my heartfelt appreciation for the outstanding care I have received at USC's Oncology Department, particularly from Dr. Lenz and Talin. Over the past few months, I've had the opportunity to meet with several specialists, and I have consistently been impressed with the professionalism, expertise, and attentiveness of the entire team. However, my experience with Dr. Lenz truly stands out. Having been through surgery for colon cancer and initially seeing another doctor for my post-op treatment plan, I was left feeling uncertain and uneasy about the direction of my care. After hearing positive recommendations from a close friend, I decided to transfer my case to USC, and I am so grateful that I did. From the moment I met Dr. Lenz, I could tell that he truly valued my input as a patient. He took the time to listen to my concerns and thoughtfully considered the treatment options available. When I mentioned the other doctor's plan to begin chemotherapy immediately, Dr. Lenz responded with a refreshing approach: he insisted on thoroughly assessing the extent of my cancer before proceeding with any treatment. His dedication to understanding the full scope of my situation, and to ensuring that my treatment plan was tailored to my specific needs, was incredibly reassuring. After a comprehensive evaluation, Dr. Lenz delivered the most wonderful news I could have hoped for, chemotherapy was not necessary at this time. That moment was a huge relief, and I couldn't have been more grateful for Dr. Lenz's thoughtful, patient centered care. His approach was a perfect balance of professionalism, empathy, and expertise. I truly felt that he saw me as more than just another case but as an individual with unique needs. While I understand that medical professionals are highly skilled in their fields, it was such a comfort to know that Dr. Lenz viewed me as more than just a diagnosis and that my concerns were taken seriously. His approach, which emphasized understanding and careful evaluation rather than jumping to treatment, gave me a renewed sense of confidence in my care. I would confidently and gladly recommend Dr. Lenz to others. As a professional myself, I believe USC is very fortunate to have a physician like Dr. Lenz.</VALUE>
